       DDDDEEEESSSSCCCCRRRRIIIIPPPPTTTTIIIIOOOONNNN
            _A_l_m_c_l_k sets an alarm at your terminal similar to the way an
            alarm clock works.  When invoked, it runs in the background
            and when the alarm goes off, it will send a message to the
            invoker's terminal(s) or to the invoker as electronic mail
            if the invoker is not logged in.  There is an optional mes-
            sage that can be specified when executing _a_l_m_c_l_k so that
            this message, rather than the default message (_A_l_a_r_m _w_e_n_t
            _o_f_f), is printed when the alarm goes off.  If the alarm is
            invoked more than eight minutes before it is due to go off,
            there is a five-minute warning issued to the terminal (but
            not sent via e-mail).

            The alarm can be terminated by executing a _k_i_l_l file that is
            placed in the invoker's bin directory when _a_l_m_c_l_k is exe-
            cuted.  It is called _k_i_l_l_a_l_m.<time>, where <time> is the
            time that the invoker specified when executing _a_l_m_c_l_k.  The
            _k_i_l_l file is removed from the invoker's bin directory either
            when the invoker executes it or when _a_l_m_c_l_k has completed.

